  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The specifications cover all points of interaction of components involved in a technical safety concept.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Details can be found in ISO 26262 Volume 4, Clause 7.4.6&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For an example of content of an HSI report it is recommended that the user refers to ISO 26262, volume 4, Annex B.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If using a model based approach it&amp;nbsp;is also possible to derive the HSI specification directly from the model using&#xD;
    an appropriate document template with the modeling tool.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>Provide information for the HW and SW teams so that they can implement their respective items.</purpose>
